OWERRI (Press Release) â€“ Governor Hope Uzodinma of Imo State has directed that all motor parks operating within the state be shut down immediately.* The directive is in furtherance of efforts by the state government to contain the spread of Coronavirus in Imo. Governor Uzodinma on Saturday announced a lockdown of the state and prohibited activities in churches, markets, marriages, burial ceremonies among others. On Monday, the governor further directed that vehicles operating within the state should stop doing so immediately and ordered that all motor parks be shut forthwith. Oguwike Nwachuku Chief Press Secretary/Media Adviser (Gov.) March 30, 2020